gpt-5-nano-2025-08-07.solvingStrategy: Identify the transformation rule from training examples. In all provided trainings, hollow 3x3 blocks (with a zero in the center) of a color remain unchanged. A vertical line (or near-linear arrangement) of a color is transformed into a row of multiple 3x3 blocks of that same color to the right of the line. The number of blocks equals the height (or length) of the line, and blocks are spaced by one blank column. The origin line is removed, leaving zeros in its place. This explains Example 1: a vertical line of color 3 becomes three 3x3 blocks of 3 to the right of the line, while hollow squares of colors 8 and 2 remain intact. Examples 2 and 3 show similar propagation for other colors when a line-like structure exists, with other non-line shapes remaining unchanged.
keySteps: Parse training examples to identify recurring shapes: hollow 3x3 blocks (e.g., 8, 2, 5, 6) and vertical/horizontal line structures in other colors (e.g., 3 in Example 1).
If a color forms a vertical line of length L, generate L consecutive 3x3 blocks of that color positioned to the right of the line, aligned with the line's top, separated by one blank column.
Remove the original line cells from the grid (set to zero) while keeping hollow 3x3 shapes and other non-line shapes intact.

Apply the same rule consistently to the test case: transform the 4-color vertical segment into two 3x3 blocks at the right of column 10 (rows 4-6), and transform the 2-color vertical segment (rows 7-9, column 10) into three 3x3 blocks at the same row span (rows 7-9) with the proper left boundaries (11-13, 15-17, 19-21). Preserve the hollow 8-block at rows 7-9, cols 6-8.
gpt-5-nano-2025-08-07.patternDescription: Transform any vertical line of a color C (length L) into L 3x3 blocks of color C placed to the right of the line; blocks are separated by one blank column; the blocks share the line's top row; the original line is removed. Hollow 3x3 shapes stay unchanged.
hints: Best approach (algorithm): Scan grid for vertical color lines, determine their height, and replace each line with adjacent 3x3 color blocks, removing the line cells.
Math formulation: For a vertical line of color C starting at (r, c) with height H, create blocks at rows r..r+2 and columns c+1..c+3, then c+5..c+7, ..., up to H blocks. Remove cells (r..r+H-1, c).
Emojis guide: 🔎 identify vertical lines -> 🧱 place 3x3 blocks to the right -> 🧹 erase the original line cells.
